<subSubSection id="AC8E4B8151BA18D7FF5EF91BED501BF8" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51BA18D7FF5EF91BED501BF8" blockId="129.[151,1437,1596,1983]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FF5EF91BEE021AD8" bold="true" box="[199,314,1668,1695]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 7.1–8.0 mm long; superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951BA18D7FCBCF91AECF51AD8" baseAuthorityName="MacLeay" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[805,973,1669,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FCBCF91AECF51AD8" box="[805,973,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Aus. flavicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pronotal and elytral colouration (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FAF3F91AEE381A84" captionStart="FIGURES 394−404" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,166,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[209,1378,166,1885]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 394−404. Pygoluciola insularis comb. nov. 394, 395, 400 type female (MNHN); 396−399, 401−404 Andaman Islands males (NHML). 394, 397 habitus ventral; 395, 396 habitus dorsal; 398, 399 abdomen: 398 ventral; 399 dorsal; 400 type label; 401 aedeagal sheath ventral; 402−403 aedeagus: 402 ventral; 403 dorsal; 404 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508252" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508252/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Figs 394−399</figureCitation>
); orange pronotum, brown elytra with brown apex and basal ¼ orange and orange lateral margin which occupies 1/3 elytron width in one male and narrower in others. Differing most obviously in the outline of 
<date id="902A3ECA51BA18D7FAACF952EA6F1AA0" box="[1333,1367,1741,1767]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">V7</date>
9 
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FAF2F952EFC21B4C" captionStart="FIGURES 394−404" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,166,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[209,1378,166,1885]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 394−404. Pygoluciola insularis comb. nov. 394, 395, 400 type female (MNHN); 396−399, 401−404 Andaman Islands males (NHML). 394, 397 habitus ventral; 395, 396 habitus dorsal; 398, 399 abdomen: 398 ventral; 399 dorsal; 400 type label; 401 aedeagal sheath ventral; 402−403 aedeagus: 402 ventral; 403 dorsal; 404 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508252" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508252/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Figs 397, 398</figureCitation>
) which has a rounded posterior margin and the LO fills this sternite completely; in 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951BA18D7FB39F96EEA7E1B4C" baseAuthorityName="MacLeay" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1184,1350,1777,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FB39F96EEA7E1B4C" box="[1184,1350,1777,1803]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Aus. flavicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51BA18D7FF2FF88AEFE01B68" box="[182,216,1813,1839]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">V7</date>
is retracted from lateral and posterior margins and there is a well-defined and apically emarginated MPP. Female macropterous associated by label data and similarity of colouration. One of several species assigned here to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951BA18D7FF2CF8C2EE041B30" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[181,316,1885,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851BA18D7FF2CF8C2EE041B30" box="[181,316,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have an aedeagal sheath sternite terminated by a boomerang shaped piece (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FB46F8C2EA791B30" box="[1247,1345,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 394−404" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,166,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[209,1378,166,1885]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 394−404. Pygoluciola insularis comb. nov. 394, 395, 400 type female (MNHN); 396−399, 401−404 Andaman Islands males (NHML). 394, 397 habitus ventral; 395, 396 habitus dorsal; 398, 399 abdomen: 398 ventral; 399 dorsal; 400 type label; 401 aedeagal sheath ventral; 402−403 aedeagus: 402 ventral; 403 dorsal; 404 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508252" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508252/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Fig. 401</figureCitation>
), and in which the aedeagus is wider across the middle, and the membranous apical portions of the LL are wider at their bases than at their apices (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51BA18D7FE25F83AED631BF8" box="[444,603,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURES 394−404" captionStartId="130.[151,264,1905,1930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,166,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[209,1378,166,1885]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURES 394−404. Pygoluciola insularis comb. nov. 394, 395, 400 type female (MNHN); 396−399, 401−404 Andaman Islands males (NHML). 394, 397 habitus ventral; 395, 396 habitus dorsal; 398, 399 abdomen: 398 ventral; 399 dorsal; 400 type label; 401 aedeagal sheath ventral; 402−403 aedeagus: 402 ventral; 403 dorsal; 404 tergite 8 ventral with aedeagal sheath and aedeagus contained." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508252" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508252/files/figure.png" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Figs 402, 403</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
